text

## 🚀 How to Compile & Run

From the parent directory that contains the `com/` folder:

```bash
# Compile all Java files
javac com/vehicleInfoSystem/models/*.java \
      com/vehicleInfoSystem/models/enums/*.java \
      com/vehicleInfoSystem/VehicleInformationSystem.java

# Run the main class
java com.vehicleInfoSystem.VehicleInformationSystem
Alternative (if you are inside vehicle-info-system/ folder):

bash
javac com/vehicleInfoSystem/**/*.java com/vehicleInfoSystem/VehicleInformationSystem.java
java com.vehicleInfoSystem.VehicleInformationSystem
📝 Sample Interaction
text
=== Vehicle Information System ===

--- Car Details ---
Make: Toyota
Model: Camry
Year: 2020
Number of Doors (2-6): 4
Fuel Type (Petrol/Diesel/Electric): Petrol

--- Motorcycle Details ---
Make: Yamaha
Model: R1
Year: 2021
Number of Wheels (2 or 3): 2
Motorcycle Type (Sport/Cruiser/Off-road): Sport

--- Truck Details ---
Make: Volvo
Model: FH16
Year: 2019
Cargo Capacity (tons, 0-100): 25.5
Transmission Type (Manual/Automatic): Manual

=== Vehicle Details ===
Car:        Toyota Camry (2020) | Doors: 4 | Fuel: PETROL
Motorcycle: Yamaha R1 (2021) | Wheels: 2 | Type: SPORT
Truck:      Volvo FH16 (2019) | Capacity: 25.5 tons | Transmission: MANUAL
🔒 Security & Robustness
No direct SQL or shell commands – safe for local use.

All inputs are trimmed, validated, and re‑prompted on error.

Enums prevent arbitrary string injection.

try‑with‑resources ensures Scanner is closed properly.

🧪 Extending the System
You can easily add new vehicle types (e.g., ElectricScooter) by implementing the Vehicle interface and any custom interface. Add new enums for vehicle‑specific attributes.

